1 f. "Eating" includes feeding oneself from a receptacle, including a plate, cup, or
2 table, or being fed through a feeding tube or intravenously.
3 g. "Toileting" includes getting to and from the toilet and on and off the toilet, and
4 performing associated personal hygiene.
5 h. "Transferring" includes moving into or out of a bed, chair, or wheelchair.
6 2. A policy defined under this chapter may not prohibit or delay payment of policy
7 benefits to a basic care facility as defined under section 23-09.3-01 if the insured:
8 a. Meets the criteria for eligibility for benefits under the policy for care or services
9 that are medically necessary;
10 b. Is unable to perform two or more activities of daily living without supervision or
11 direct assistance; or
12 c. Has cognitive impairment requiring continual supervision.
